    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is an exceptional 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, showcasing a level of mechanical preservation rarely seen. The 13B-REW power plant features a sequential twin-turbocharger setup with zero boost lag, supported by a documented compression test yielding high, consistent pulses across all rotor faces. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise five-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The chassis retains its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and 50/50 weight balance, with no evidence of bushing fatigue or thermal stress in the engine bay. This collector-grade example is free of synchro grind and maintains a vacuum system that is fully intact and leak-free.",
